name: wood preservation facility construction, vacuum pressure vessel | wood preservation facility, vacuum pressure method | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10635/documentation

The plant has a yearly throughput of 6'000 m3 timber, a life time of 75 years and a life time output of 4.5E5 m3 treated timber. The infrastructure represents plants with pressure vessels used for vacuum pressure treatment. A more detailed description of the design of the required equipment can be found in the respective datasets for wood preservation services.

Infrastructure dataset containing the main elements of the facility.

The land area and the material (production and disposal) needed for a preservative treatment plant for oscillating pressure treatment including strorage area is included.

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from Germany and Switzerland. Location of plant within Europe of minor importance
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Infrastructure for vacuum pressure impregnation; the vessel is comparably large.
